This paper is focused on defect prediction models, which are commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the impact of different classification techniques and performance measures, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of statistical models to understand the impact of class rebalancing techniques is also relevant to statistical learning (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of class rebalancing techniques on the accuracy of defect prediction models, which is relevant to computer security (cs.CR).
